00:00:24.630 --> 00:00:29.210
really share the same underlying concept like leaf and leaves.

00:00:30.560 --> 00:00:34.070
And in these cases we're going to do what's called stemming.

00:00:34.070 --> 00:00:39.690
Stemming removes the prefixes and the post fixes, the suffixes to the words,

00:00:39.690 --> 00:00:44.620
and just uses the root word as the corresponding candidate and class.

00:00:44.620 --> 00:00:48.860
That leaves us with a question that you, you, you indicated both counter and

00:00:48.860 --> 00:00:50.380
count, okay?

